The paper deals with the problem of finding a triangulation of a planar point set or a simple polygon that minimizes the expected distance between two points. This problem is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions several open problems, which suggests that it may be of interest to researchers in game theory (cs.GT) as well.
